Nov 15 2009 	Awesome Value in NYC	First off, this place is not for divas who have no clue about the realities of downtown New York City. If you expect silence, stay home: this is a loud neighbourhood possibly close to an ambulance dispatch but also amazingly close to the subway and some must-see Real New York attractions, and by that I do not mean Katz's Deli. It is walking distance from Little Italy and Chinatown and better yet, on the verge of the historic Lower East Side and East Village eateries to die for. Plus, if you want to explore Brooklyn you are not so far away: Williamsburg is right across the water.The Gem is clean, amazingly priced for the awesome location, staffed by wonderful courteous people and sure, it is low on extras like you may be used to at some mondo chain hotels. But the in room coffee is to die for and the shower is hot. The room is clean and well-appointed given the close quarters and frankly, I would stay here again in a heartbeat. I really appreciated the efforts made and while the sleeping may not be easy, they did mention in the hype that this is the city that never sleeps...The Gem's a keeper for me.	
