Aug 9 2009 	Glad I chose to stay here!	I was very pleased with the GEM SoHo. The location is great if the hustle and bustle of midtown is not what you are looking for. Houston is busy, but I felt very relaxed once I got into my room. The atmosphere in the GEM is cozy and quiet. I did wear earplugs to sleep, but the outside noise really wasn't that bad.  The front desk staff are very friendly, helpful and courteous. It was nice to be greeted with a smile every day. The room was small, but clean and comfy. The bed and linens were top-notch. It was great to have the fridge and microwave. The hotel is just across the street from Whole Foods, a small park, and tons of excellent little restaurants. Don't miss Russ &amp; Daughters just down Houston for an amazing bagel, lox and cream cheese breakfast. I did not miss room service at all, and felt I benefited from trying the unique local spots in the neighborhood. My friends stayed in midtown in a big chain hotel and paid lots more for the fancy trimmings, but I was very happy with this little place in the village. A big chain hotel is the same anywhere, but the GEM made for a unique experience. I would stay here again.	
Aug 2 2009 	One sweet hotel!	We stayed at the GEM for one night for a wedding. Hotel is located right on the edge of Soho in a lively part of town, directly above the NY institution, Yonah Schimmel's Knishes, and convenient walking distance to the East Village, Little Italy, and Chinatown. The rooms, hallways and lobby are all quite COMPACT but nicely appointed, and as accommodating as they can be given the tight quarters. Staff were very friendly &amp; helpful, including holding our bags for several hours in the small office. We reserved one room with 2 beds but were reassigned to 2 rooms on the same floor (not adjacent) which worked out fine and ended up being a big bargain (we were charged the single room rate, as is appropriate). Room appointments were lovely &amp; I wish I could have enjoyed the room more - we were out at our event for the bulk of the time. Nice shower, toiletries, coffee, fridge/microwave, and very comfy beds, linens, and bathrobes. Poor sleepers should note that Houston Street is ALWAYS noisy. Bring earplugs. Also, for those traveling by car - and good luck traveling by car in lower Manhattan - there is no parking, but many commercial parking garages around. The staff recommended one east of the hotel, but we found parking on Elizabeth St. just north of Houston and it worked out great.I would happily give 5 stars except for a few modest issues: one room's door did NOT want to latch shut, so we had to use the deadbolt simply to close the door; the same room had a sketchy bathroom light switch; and - worst - we were at first assigned to a room that was already occupied. Big no-no, mitigated by the fact it was occupied by other people attending the same event (but not known to us). No one likes to be getting changed &amp; have a stranger walk into their hotel room!! That said, this was an great value for an elegant and comfortable hotel experience. I would definitely return.	
Jul 7 2009 	Impressed	Booked the GEM hotel soho based on the reasonable price and reviews read on trip advisor. Arrived and was very impressed. I'm not your typical boutique hotel person but my experience here has totally changed my mind.Area:The hotel is conveniently located in the lower east side, metro stops easily within walking distance and a nice basketball park across the street. Whole foods also across the street and great restaurants all around. If your looking for a morning coffee spot I used Sugar a block east or upstairs at Whole Foods. Both good coffee spots. Hotel is within walking distance to Mulberry street, china town, gramercy and soho. Broadway offers some great shopping as well which is close by. Metro stop is close and can't get you anywhere in the city quickly. The Room:The room is small.. basically you walk in have a bathroom on your way in, nice vanity, shower and sink. Then you have a queen size bed with a desk and a flat screen tv. It was the perfect size. Really you come back from being out all day and relax on your bed and watch tv. What I really liked and didn't see in any one else's review was that each room has a mini fridge and microwave. This was great for holding beer, breakfast foods etc. We never used the microwave but i'm sure a lot of other people do. Room was clean, bed was extremely comfortable, street noise was non- existent, we had a room on the 3rd floor right above the street. So if that is your concern, request a room above the 2nd floor.Overall:Great hotel, perfect for a couple or a single, wouldn't recommend for families, even though I did see some families there. Ride to laguardia is about $25 bucks cab ride and you can't get there via subway. Would highly recommend it to all my friends as an affordable, classy, safe, comfortable place to stay and see New York.	
